      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SEASIDE DRIVE (3) was a beaten favourite on her return at her latest appearance here a week ago but there was still merit in her performance, leading and finishing 3.2 metres away in third. Fitter for that and draws to push forward again so can atone. THREETWONINE (2) has been about the mark in recent runs, making it four placings from her last five starts when she came from a wide barrier and finished 2 metres away in third at the latest appearance at Newcastle. Has the benefit of a good draw so could break through. KINGS FURY (11) will be fitter second-up. Cam Hart goes on and has a strong record on him. Expecting big improvement. LEWIE KELLY (7) has placed in both previous second-up attempts so should be fitter for the resuming fifth at Goulburn. Draws for a trail and his lone win came at this circuit and distance.",
